Common word order mistakes in Spanish writing include placing adjectives before nouns instead of after, as is typical in Spanish, and confusing the structure of phrases, such as using the wrong order in compound nouns. 

Additionally, learners often struggle with the placement of subject pronouns, which can be omitted in many cases.

Common Word Order Mistakes in Spanish Writing

Incorrect Placement of Adjectives

In Spanish, adjectives typically follow the nouns they describe. 

Many learners mistakenly place adjectives before nouns, which can lead to confusion.

Correct: 
(a big house)
una casa grande 
una NOUN ADJ 
una NOUN[-sa](v) ADJ[-de] 

Incorrect: 
una grande casa
una ADJ NOUN 
una ADJ[-de] NOUN[-sa](v)


Mixing Up Subject and Verb Order

Spanish often allows for flexibility in word order, but beginners may struggle with the standard Subject-Verb-Object (SVO) structure. 

Dropping the subject pronoun is common, but it can lead to awkward sentences if not done correctly.

Correct: 
I eat apple
Como  manzana
como NOUN 
como NOUN[-na](v) 
    
Incorrect: 
Yo como manzana (it's less natural)
yo como NOUN 
yo como NOUN[-na](v) 


Misplacing Indefinite Articles

When stating occupations, Spanish does not use an indefinite article. 

Learners often translate directly from English, leading to errors.

Correct: 
(I am a teacher)
Soy profesora
soy NOUN 
soy NOUN[-ra](v)
    
Incorrect:
Soy una profesora
soy una NOUN 
soy una NOUN[-ra](v) 

Confusing "Ser" and "Estar"

Both verbs mean "to be," but they are used in different contexts. Mixing them up can change the meaning of a sentence.

Correct: 
Soy feliz (I am happy - a permanent state)
soy ADJ 
soy ADJ[-iz] 

Incorrect: 
Estoy feliz (implies a temporary state)
estoy ADJ 
estoy ADJ[-iz] 

Incorrect Use of Prepositions

Using the wrong preposition can alter the intended meaning. For example, confusing "por" and "para" is a common mistake.

Correct: 
Este regalo es para ti (This gift is for you)
este NOUN es para ti 
este NOUN[-lo](v) es para ti 

Incorrect: 
Este regalo es por ti
este NOUN es por ti 
este NOUN[-lo](v) es por ti 




